                    </header>
                    <div class="image fit">
                        <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/800x400" alt="Engine Rebuild">
                        <hr>
                        <p>The objective of this project was to restore the engine's performance and reliability by replacing critical components and enhancing its aesthetic appeal.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Head Bolts Replacement Section -->
    <section id="head-bolts" class="wrapper style2">
        <div class="inner">
            <div class="box">
                <div class="content">
                    <header class="align-center">
                        <h2>Head Bolts Replacement</h2>
                    </header>
                    <div class="image fit">
                        <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/800x400" alt="ARP Head Bolt Kit">
                        <hr>
                        <p>During the disassembly, I discovered that the existing head bolts were torque-to-yield (TTY) types, which are designed for single use and must be replaced after removal. To ensure optimal engine performance and durability, I decided to replace them with high-quality ARP head bolts. This required ordering the new bolts and waiting for their arrival, which took about a day.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Valve Cover Repainting Section -->
    <section id="valve-covers" class="wrapper style2">
        <div class="inner">
            <div class="box">
                <div class="content">
                    <header class="align-center">
                        <h2>Valve Cover Repainting</h2>
                    </header>
                    <div class="image fit">
                        <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/800x400" alt="Valve Cover Before and After">
                        <hr>
                        <p>While awaiting the arrival of the new head bolts, I took the opportunity to enhance the engine's appearance by repainting the valve covers. The original covers had become worn and discolored over time. After thorough cleaning and preparation, I applied a fresh coat of high-temperature engine enamel, resulting in a revitalized look. Below is a side-by-side comparison of the valve covers before and after repainting.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

